org.eclipse.viatra.cep.core.engine.runtime

Class EvaluationPatterns

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.incquery.runtime.api.impl.BasePatternGroup
      • org.eclipse.incquery.runtime.api.impl.BaseGeneratedPatternGroup
        • org.eclipse.viatra.cep.core.engine.runtime.EvaluationPatterns
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.eclipse.incquery.runtime.api.IQueryGroup

    public final class EvaluationPatterns
extends org.eclipse.incquery.runtime.api.impl.BaseGeneratedPatternGroup
    A pattern group formed of all patterns defined in evaluationPatterns.eiq.

    Use the static instance as any org.eclipse.incquery.runtime.api.IPatternGroup, to conveniently prepare an EMF-IncQuery engine for matching all patterns originally defined in file evaluationPatterns.eiq, in order to achieve better performance than one-by-one on-demand matcher initialization.

    From package org.eclipse.viatra.cep.core.engine.runtime, the group contains the definition of the following patterns:

    • latestEvent
    • finishedAutomaton
    • tokenInTrapState
    • enabledTransition
    • eventProcessedByEventToken
    • partiallyMatchedEventPattern
    • initState
    • tokenEntersTimedZone
    • tokenLeavesTimedZone
    • tokenInTimedZone
    See Also:
    IPatternGroup
